e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[Sylvan yellow fever in South America runs in 5-7 year cycles. The last
peak in Brazil was 74 cases (17 deaths) in 1993. Travelers to the Amazon
should get themselves vaccinated. Travelers to other parts of Brazil need
not worry. - Mod.JW
